      • getCurrencyXPath

        public java.lang.String getCurrencyXPath()
        This function returns the currencyXPath. It is supported for disabled text box, label and table columns. In case of table columns the currencyXPath will be taken from the root of the model unless isCurrencyXPathRepeating is specified as true, else currencyXPath will be taken as the relative binding. i.e. binding after the repeating element.

      • getImageServerConfigName

      • setServerImageConfiguration

        public void setServerImageConfiguration(java.lang.String imageServerConfigName)
        Sets the configuration for getting the images form the server. Once the imageServerConfigName is set to a not null value, the images will be fetched from the server and applied to the table column.
        Parameters:
        imageServerConfigName - Name of the configuration to be used to fetch the images from the server.

      • setCurrencyXPath

        public void setCurrencyXPath(java.lang.String currencyXPath)
        This function sets the currencyXPath to the value from where to get the currency. It is supported for disabled text box, label and table columns. In case of table columns the currencyXPath will be taken from the root of the model unless isCurrencyXPathRepeating is specified as true, else currencyXPath will be taken as the relative binding. i.e. binding after the repeating element.
        Parameters:
        currencyXPath -

        public void setDefaultServerImageProvider(IYRCDefaultServerImageProvider defaultServerImageProvider)
        Sets the default server image provider for the table column. If the default server image provider is set, then the default image configured in the image location is not applied instead, the provider is asked for providing the default image.

      • setCheckBoxHorizontalAlignment

        public void setCheckBoxHorizontalAlignment(int checkBoxHorizontalAlignment)
        Allows user to set Alignment of the tableColumn CheckBox

        Alignments:
        SWT.LEFT, SWT.RIGHT, SWT.CENTER
        Default:
        SWT.CENTER

        Note: Only one of the possible alignments SWT.LEFT, SWT.RIGHT and SWT.CENTER may be specified.

        IMPORTANT: This method works only if the table column editor is set as check box

        Parameters:
        checkBoxHorizontalAlignment -
        See Also:
        YRCTableBindingData.setCellTypes(String[])

      • getFileUploadType

        public java.lang.String getFileUploadType()
        Method to get the file upload type which can be ONSELECT or ONSUBMIT. ONSELECT indicates the file needs to be uploaded as soon as the file is registered . ONSUBMIT indicates the file will have to be uploaded to the server before API which persists the File in DB is called
        Returns:
        file upload type
